30 authorizes the use of a short trial, in addition to any other appropriate provisions, the rules and
31 procedures governing a short trial must authorize the short trial judge to award to the
32 prevailing party attorney’s fees in an amount not to exceed $15,000, as provided by specific
33 statute or court rule.
34 [Existing law provides that if an action is submitted to arbitration and, after arbitration, a
35 party requests a trial anew before a jury: (1) the written findings made by the arbitrator or the
36 panel of arbitrators must be admitted at trial; and (2) the court is required to give a specific
37 instruction to the jury. (NRS 38.259) Section 4 of this bill removes such requirements.]
38 Sections 1, 1.5 and 3 make a conforming change to apply the definition of the term
39 “short trial” to the provisions of this bill.
