1 Section 1. Chapter 38 of NRS is hereby amended by adding thereto a new
2 section to read as follows:
3 As used in NRS 38.250 to 38.259, inclusive, unless the context otherwise
4 requires, “short trial” means a trial that is conducted, with the consent of the
5 parties to the action, in accordance with procedures designed to limit the length
6 of the trial, including, without limitation, restrictions on the amount of discovery
7 requested by each party, the use of a jury composed of not more than eight
8 persons and a specified limit on the amount of time each party may use to present
9 the party’s case.
